messages.message: Not sure how to send a link but the project is called '_Period end date test (21)_' - let me know if you can't see it. Note: the first two bank statements have the hyphen format and generate errors. The third statement also has a hyphen format, but because the dates are the same the tool picks up the correct date.

@nick.talbert the link for the project is the URL of the page when you have the Build project open

 could you share that URL?

@Jasper yes we’ve received a few reports  (https://instabase.slack.com/archives/C05BJCNKZAM/p1733761959022299)of extraction performing differently in Build since 24.48 was deployed to prod

we expect these to be resolved when we upgrade the default model from gpt-3.5-1106 to gpt-4o-mini (likely 25.02, GA Jan 21)
Got it, thanks @Serena. Feel free to delete the bug ticket in that case.

btw i found Nick’s project here https://aihub.instabase.com/build/0193ca8b-e49c-7602-b543-b53a59153276

@Kaustubh (KD) if you’re curious, you can open it by logging in as <mailto:support-testing+aihubib@instabase.com|support-testing+aihubib@instabase.com> - you can find the credentials for this account in 1password
@Kaustubh (KD) and to answer your question, this “Period end date” field is using the standard model, not the advanced model
@Serena is the result correct if you change the model to "Advanced"?
yes, the result is correct if the model is changed to “Advanced”

using the standard model, i can get the right date by just editing the description to be a bit more descriptive; this is the description i put for a field name `period end date`
```The ending date of the statement period```
and this gives the correct date
Thanks all for the feedback and teaching me! Really appreciate it
